      "text": "SPP Market Storage Resources and FERC Order 841 | PCI[Skip to content] \n[] \n[Contact] \n[Set Up A Call] \n* [![]] \n* [Blog] \n* [] SPP Market Storage Resources and FERC Order 841\n##### Share this post\n![Picture of Patrick McGarry] \n#### Patrick McGarry\n![] \n# SPP Market Storage Resources and FERC Order 841\n**June 15, 2021\n/\n[US ISO/RTO Markets] \n#### A Three-Part Blog Series\nPart 1: Southwest Power Pool Market Storage Resources\nOn February 15, 2018, the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC) issued Order 841, a landmark, unanimous, bipartisan order directing regional grid operators to remove impediments to electric storage participation in[wholesale power] markets. More than three years later, markets are finally implementing the changes required under the order, enabling Energy Storage Resources (ESR) to provide services that they&#8217;re technically capable of providing.\nFor a variety of reasons, the heavy lifting required to implement these changes has caused some delays. On May ",
